<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Schema: assembly_module_usage_view_mim
<express_ref linkend="assembly_module_usage_view:mim:assembly_module_usage_view_mim"/>
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="assembly_module_usage_view_mim">
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Entity: Assembly_definition
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Assembly_module_usage_view_mim.assembly_definition">
An <b>assembly_definition</b> is a  <express_ref linkend="Physical_unit_usage_view:mim:Physical_unit_usage_view_mim.physical_unit"/>.  An <b>assembly_definition</b> implements
the ARM concepts of a  <express_ref linkend="Assembly_module_design:arm:Assembly_module_design_arm.Pca"/> and
a  <express_ref linkend="Assembly_module_usage_view:arm:Assembly_module_usage_view_arm.Pca_usage_view"/>.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
WR: Assembly_definition.WR1
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Assembly_module_usage_view_mim.assembly_definition.wr:wr1">
The name shall exist.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
WR: Assembly_definition.WR2
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Assembly_module_usage_view_mim.assembly_definition.wr:wr2">
The <b>assembly_definition</b> shall be a definition of a product that has a name of 'assembly module'.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
WR: Assembly_definition.WR3
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Assembly_module_usage_view_mim.assembly_definition.wr:wr3">
If the <b>assembly_definition</b> is a physical design, it shall relate to exactly
one <b>assembly_definition</b>, externally_defined_assembly_definition, or 
library_defined_assembly_definition that is a physical design usage with a 
name of 'assembly module' as the design usage.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
WR: Assembly_definition.WR4
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Assembly_module_usage_view_mim.assembly_definition.wr:wr4">
If the <b>assembly_definition</b> has a frame_of_reference name of 'physical design
usage', it shall have at least two shape_aspects that are 
assembly_module_terminals with a description of 'pca terminal'.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Entity: Assembly_module_interface_terminal
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Assembly_module_usage_view_mim.assembly_module_interface_terminal">
<note> The local rules for this entity have not been fully updated to agree with the changes in clause 4.2.</note><p>

An <b>assembly_module_interface_terminal</b> is an  <express_ref linkend="Assembly_module_usage_view:mim:Assembly_module_usage_view_mim.assembly_module_terminal"/> that implement the
ARM concept of  <express_ref linkend="Assembly_module_usage_view:arm:Assembly_module_usage_view_arm.Assembly_module_interface_terminal"/>
</p></ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
Entity: Assembly_module_terminal
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Assembly_module_usage_view_mim.assembly_module_terminal"><p>
An <b>assembly_module_terminal</b> is a  <express_ref linkend="product_property_definition_schema:ir_express:product_property_definition_schema.shape_aspect"/> that implement the ARM concepts of: 
</p><ul>
<li> <express_ref linkend="Assembly_module_usage_view:arm:Assembly_module_usage_view_arm.Assembly_module_terminal"/></li>
<li> <express_ref linkend="Part_terminal:arm:Part_terminal_arm.Part_terminal"/></li>
<li> <express_ref linkend="Assembly_module_usage_view:arm:Assembly_module_usage_view_arm.Pca_terminal"/></li>
</ul>
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
WR: Assembly_module_terminal.WR1
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Assembly_module_usage_view_mim.assembly_module_terminal.wr:wr1">
The  <express_ref linkend="product_definition_schema:ir_express:product_definition_schema.product_definition"/> name shall exist. 
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
WR: Assembly_module_terminal.WR2
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Assembly_module_usage_view_mim.assembly_module_terminal.wr:wr2">
The <b>assembly_module_terminal</b> shall be the  <express_ref linkend="product_property_definition_schema:ir_express:product_property_definition_schema.shape_aspect"/> of a  <express_ref linkend="product_definition_schema:ir_express:product_definition_schema.product_definition"/> of a product that has a name of 'assembly module'.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
WR: Assembly_module_terminal.WR3
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Assembly_module_usage_view_mim.assembly_module_terminal.wr:wr3">
The <b>assembly_module_terminal</b> shall have at least one
 <express_ref linkend="product_property_representation_schema:ir_express:product_property_representation_schema.shape_representation"/>.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
WR: Assembly_module_terminal.WR4
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Assembly_module_usage_view_mim.assembly_module_terminal.wr:wr4">
The <b>assembly_module_terminal</b> shall be related to at most one 
 <express_ref linkend="Part_terminal:mim:Part_terminal_mim.part_connected_terminals_definition"/> as a 'member connected terminal'.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
WR: Assembly_module_terminal.WR5
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Assembly_module_usage_view_mim.assembly_module_terminal.wr:wr5">
If the <b>assembly_module_terminal</b> has a description of 'pca terminal',
it shall be an aspect of the shape of an  <express_ref linkend="Assembly_module_usage_view:mim:Assembly_module_usage_view_mim.assembly_definition"/>, 
externally_defined_assembly_definition, or library_defined_assembly_definition 
that has a frame_of_reference name 'physical design usage'.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
WR: Assembly_module_terminal.WR6
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Assembly_module_usage_view_mim.assembly_module_terminal.wr:wr6">
The <b>assembly_module_terminal</b> shall be related to exactly one  <express_ref linkend="product_property_definition_schema:ir_express:product_property_definition_schema.shape_aspect"/> with 
a description of 'connection zone'.
</ext_description>

<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
WR: Assembly_module_terminal.WR7
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Assembly_module_usage_view_mim.assembly_module_terminal.wr:wr7">
The <b>assembly_module_terminal</b> shall be related to at most one  <express_ref linkend="product_property_definition_schema:ir_express:product_property_definition_schema.shape_aspect"/> with a description of 'interface terminal'.
</ext_description>

</ext_descriptions>
